<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Charlotte Schools Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- The Associated Press, in a Sept. 10 story  
about the end of court-ordered busing to achieve racial balance in 
Charlotte schools, misreported the year of a U.S. Supreme Court 
ruling in the case. 
</P>
<P>
	A federal judge's decision had launched the busing in 1969. The  
U.S. Supreme Court upheld that decision in 1971 in its ruling in 
Swann vs. the Charlotte-Mecklenburg Board of Education. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
