<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia 0, Manchester United 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Croatia Zagreb held defending champion Manchester United to a  
scoreless tie Tuesday night on the first day of play in the 
expanded European Champions Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United, 6-0-1 this season in England's Premier  
League, was expected to dominate, especially playing at home in Old 
Trafford. Teddy Sheringham had a chance to win it for the Reds in 
the final minute but his shot was blocked by goalkeeper Drazen 
Ladic. 
</P>
<P>
	In the other Group D game, Olympique Marseille beat Sturm Graz  
2-0 on goals by Robert Pires in the ninth minute and Fabrizio 
Ravanelli in the 33rd. 
</P>
<P>
	Barcelona came from behind to win on the road, beating AIK  
Stockholm on goals by Abelardo and Dani in the final four minutes. 
Abelardo headed in a corner kick in the 86th minute and Dani headed 
in Rivaldo's free kick in the 90th. Nebojsa Novakovic had put the 
home team ahead in the 72nd. 
</P>
<P>
	In the other Group B game Fiorentina goalkeeper Francesco Toldo  
smothered Nwankwo Kanu's penalty kick with 10 minutes left during a 
scoreless tie against Arsenal at Florence. 
</P>
<P>
	Slovenia's Maribor won 1-0 at Dynamo Kiev in Group A on Ante  
Simundza's goal in the 73rd minute. Lazio of Rome played a 1-1 tie 
at Bayer Leverkusen in the group's other game. Oliver Neuville's 
shot off a cross from Thomas Reichenberger in the 14th minute 
deflected off Alessandro Nesta and beat goalkeeper Luca 
Marchegiani, but Lazio tied the score four minutes later on Sinisa 
Mihajlovic's spectacular 25-yard free kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Norway's Rosenborg won 3-0 at Portugal's Boavista in Group C on  
goals by Jan Derek Sorensen (ninth minute), Orjan Berg (43rd) and 
Roar Strand (75th). 
</P>
<P>
	Feyenoord of Rotterdam tied visiting Borussia Dortmund 1-1 in  
the other game. Feyenoord's Kees van Wonderen scored off a 
give-and-go with Julio Ricardo Cruz in the 67th minute, but Fredi 
Bobic tied it four minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
	Wednesday's schedule has Olympiakos-Real Madrid and Molde-FC  
Porto in Group E, Bayern Munich-PSV Eindhoven and Valencia-Glasgow 
Rangers in Group F; Sparta Prague-Bordeaux and Willem II 
Tilburg-Spartak Moscow in Group G; and Chelsea-AC Milan and 
Galatasaray-Hertha Berlin in Group H. 
</P>
<P>
	Each team plays six games in the first round, with the top two  
teams in each group advancing. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
