<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kris S. Colt Sells for Record $3.9M </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- A bay yearling colt by Kris S. sold for a  
record $3.9 million Tuesday during the second day of the Keeneland 
September Yearling Sale. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheikh Mohammed, crown prince of Dubai, United Arab Emirates,  
and owner of Godolphin Racing stable, bought the colt, who was 
consigned by Dixiana Farm as agent for Harold Harrison. The colt is 
out of the Mr. Prospector mare Mr. P's Princess. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the highest price paid for a yearling at Keeneland in  
September since the sale began in 1944. The previous record was set 
in 1997 when Satish Sanan and his Padua Stables purchased a son of 
Mr. Prospector for $2.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
	On the first day of the 11-day sale, Keeneland sold seven  
yearlings for $1 million or more. On Tuesday, 14 yearlings went for 
$1 million or more, three more than in the entire September 1998 
sale. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, Keeneland sold 254 yearlings for $69,727,000. The  
average was $274,516 and the median was $147,500. A year ago, 
Keeneland sold 272 yearlings for $46,495,000. The average was 
$170,938 and the median was $100,000. This year's average is up 
60.6 percent and the median is up 47.5 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Over the first two days of the sale, Keeneland has sold 471  
yearlings for $120,889,000. The average is $256,665 and the median 
is $150,000. A year ago, Keeneland sold 523 head for $90,016,000 
for an average of $172,115 and a median of $105,000. The average is 
up 49.1 percent and the median is up 42 percent over the two days. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
