<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lopez, Chavez on Boxing Card </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Ricardo Lopez, the unbeaten WBC 105-pound  
champion, will challenge Will Grigsby for the IBF 108-pound title 
Oct. 2, on a card that will also feature Julio Caesar Chavez, a 
former champion in three weight classes. 
</P>
<P>
	Chavez, of Mexico, will box Willy Wise, of Westbury, N.Y., in  
10-round bout, and if he wins he will challenge WBC champion Kostya 
Tszyu of Australia for the WBC super lightweight (140 pounds) title 
early next year, promoter Don King said Tuesday at a news 
conference. 
</P>
<P>
	The show at the Las Vegas Hilton will be televised by Showtime.  
</P>
<P>
	Lopez, of Mexico, will take a 47-0-1 record, with 35 knockouts,  
into the fight against Grigsby, of St. Paul, Minn., who has only a 
14-1-1 record, with six knockouts, since turning pro in 1988. He 
did not fight from 1990 to '93. It will be Lopez's second title 
defense. 
</P>
<P>
	Chavez (101-3-2, 84 knockouts) has two losses and a draw in his  
last three title fights. He was stopped in the fourth round by 
Oscar De La Hoya when he lost the WBC super lightweight title, 
fought to a draw when he tried to regain that title against Miguel 
Angel Gonzalez in 1998 and was stopped in the eighth round by De La 
Hoya in a bid to win the WBC welterweight title last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Wise has a 23-6-4 record, with seven knockouts.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
