<HEADLINE> 'Stigmata' No. 1 at Box Office / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``Stigmata'' led a trio of horror films that  
dominated the weekend box office, earning $18.3 million and bumping 
``The Sixth Sense'' from its five-week reign as the nation's most 
popular movie. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Sixth Sense,'' with Bruce Willis as a therapist who aids a  
boy tormented by ghosts, earned $16.5 million for second place. 
``Stir of Echoes,'' starring Kevin Bacon, was in third place with a 
$5.8 million take. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled Monday by Exhibitor Relations Co. 
Inc. and ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Stigmata,'' MGM, $18.3 million, 2,899 locations, $6,316  
average, $18.3 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Sixth Sense,'' Disney, $16.5 million, 2,782 locations,  
$5,935 average, $197.6 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Stir of Echoes,'' Artisan, $5.8 million, 1,888 locations,  
$3,078 average, $5.8 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``Runaway Bride,'' Paramount, $3.8 million, 2,773 locations,  
$1,383 average, $140.4 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Bowfinger,'' Universal, $3.6 million, 2,452 locations,  
$1,470 average, $60.4 million, five weeks. 
</P>
