<HEADLINE> Sweden Davis Cup Team Has Injuries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) -- With two of his top players injured,  
Sweden's Davis Cup coach Carl-Axel Hageskog on Tuesday announced 
the team that will try to beat Austria and prevent Sweden from 
being relegated from the World Group. 
</P>
<P>
	Sweden has managed to belong to the top 16-nation group ever  
since it was introduced in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sept. 24-26 match will be played on a clay court at the  
Austrian city of Klagenfurt, with the winner qualifying for the 
World Group in next year's competition. 
</P>
<P>
	Since the match is being played on clay, Sweden's top-ranked  
player, Thomas Enqvist, will not play. Also missing the tie are 
Thomas Johansson and Jonas Bjorkman, both out with injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	Hageskog nominated Magnus Gustafsson and Magnus Norman for  
singles and Mikael Tillstrom to team up with Nicklas Kulti in the 
doubles. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
