<HEADLINE> College Athlete Dies After Aneurysm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FERRUM, Va. (AP) -- Ferrum College basketball player Brian Reed  
died Tuesday from a brain aneurysm, a day after collapsing in the 
college's weight room. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors said the aneurysm was natural and not brought on by the  
workout, the school said. 
</P>
<P>
	Reed, 19, died shortly before 8 p.m. when he was taken off life  
support at Carilion Roanoke Memorial Hospital, school spokesman 
Matt Conn said. Reed had collapsed while working out in the weight 
room at about 4:23 p.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Emergency personnel responded to a call for help at 4:30 p.m.,  
said Claude Webster, director of public safety for Franklin County. 
Rescue workers found Reed, of Virginia Beach, unconscious but 
breathing on the floor, Webster said. 
</P>
<P>
	Reed's breathing became labored as he was transported to  
Carilion Franklin Memorial Hospital, and he was immediately 
airlifted to Roanoke Memorial. 
</P>
<P>
	Reed, a 6-foot-5 forward on the basketball team, was studying  
for a dual major in computer science and information systems. He 
also played football last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
