<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 14:00:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> College Football Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Nick Davis likes a challenge, which is why he wants Wisconsin to  
begin its Big Ten Conference schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	Davis and the ninth-ranked Badgers (2-0) have to wait another  
week: it's Cincinnati on Saturday before their two biggest games of 
the season -- No. 6 Michigan at home on Sept. 25; at No. 13 Ohio 
State the following week. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have some momentum, but I think the next game we can get  
even more momentum,'' Davis, the Badgers' kick and punt return 
whiz, said. ``Playing the Big Ten teams, that's our conference, and 
we want to get rolling. We are really on a roll.'' 
</P>
<P>
	While the Badgers' Ron Dayne chases Ricky Williams' year-old  
career rushing record, Davis was on a roll of his own last week in 
a 50-10 rout of Ball State. He ran up 227 all-purpose yards, 
including a 77-yard TD run on a free kick following a safety. He 
also had four catches for 91 yards subbing at wide receiver for the 
injured Chris Chambers. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *CLUB NFL:* Pretty good so far for some former NFL coaches who  
jumped back into the college ranks this season: 
</P>
<P>
	John Robinson, former Los Angeles Rams coach and two-time  
Southern California coach, is 2-0 at UNLV, a team that had a 
16-game losing streak when he took over. 
</P>
<P>
	Dennis Erickson, former Seattle Seahawks and Miami Hurricanes  
coach, is 2-0 at Oregon State, which is after its first winning 
season since 1970. 
</P>
<P>
	June Jones, former Atlanta Falcons and San Diego Chargers coach,  
is 1-1 at Hawaii, which just beat Eastern Illinois 31-27 to end 
major college's longest losing streak at 19 games. 
</P>
<P>
	And then there's Kevin Steele, former Carolina Panthers  
assistant, who is 0-2 at Baylor. One loss came on a missed extra 
point in overtime, the other last Saturday when the Bears fumbled 
on the last play of the game only to have it returned 99 yards by 
UNLV for the winning points. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
 *Around the conferences: 	
</P>
<P>
                               *ACC 	
</P>
<P>
	Georgia Tech QB Joe Hamilton had the best day of his career in a  
41-35 loss last week at Florida State. His 22-of-25 for 387 yards 
and four TDs pushed him to No. 1 in the nation in passing 
efficiency. ... LaMont Jordan's three rushing TDs against Western 
Carolina last week was the most for a Maryland player since Rick 
Badanjek had three against North Carolina in 1984. ... Florida 
State had six turnovers in last year's 24-7 loss at NC State. In 
seven games against the Wolfpack since joining the ACC in 1992, the 
Seminoles averaged 44.7 points and 524.9 yards. ... Virginia, 
looking to rebound from its loss at Clemson, takes on Wake Forest, 
a team the Cavs have beaten 15 times in a row. ... North Carolina 
sophomore Ronald Curry tied a career-best with 19 completions for 
241 yards in the Tar Heels' win at Indiana. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                             *Big East    	
</P>
<P>
	Syracuse is 2-0 for the first time since 1993. Next up, No. 6  
Michigan at the Carrier Dome. ... Temple TB Elmarko Jackson and WR 
Carlos Johnson missed last week's 40-0 loss at Kansas State and are 
questionable for Saturday's game at Akron. ... Penn State is 19-3 
vs. Big East teams since the conference began playing football in 
'91. ... Pittsburgh has lost seven in a row to Penn State. ... 
Miami takes an eight-game winning streak over Big Ten teams into 
Saturday's game against the Nittany Lions. The Hurricanes' last 
loss to a Big Ten team was Sept. 8, 1984 -- 22-14 at Michigan. ... 
In its previous four games against Kent, Pittsburgh has outscored 
the Golden Flashes 158-35. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                              *Big Ten    	
</P>
<P>
	QB Antwaan Randle El ran for 62 yards in Indiana's loss to North  
Carolina last week, giving him 1,053 for his career. He's the only 
Hoosiers QB with five 100-yard rushing games. Randle El needs 31 
yards rushing to set the Indiana career record for a quarterback 
(1,083, Harry Gonso, 1967-69). ... Ohio State (42-20 winner over 
UCLA) won its 21st straight home opener, dating back to Art 
Schlichter's freshman debut in 1978. ... The Buckeyes move into the 
second week of an unprecedented five-game homestand. The Bucks have 
never played more than four in a row at home. Next up is Ohio, 
followed by Cincinnati. Ohio State hasn't played in-state opponents 
on consecutive weeks since meeting Wittenberg and Ohio Wesleyan to 
open the 1926 season. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                              *Big 12    	
</P>
<P>
	With their 38-21 win over Rutgers, the Texas Longhorns moved to  
200-2 in games where they have scored 35 or more points. ... The 
Texas offensive line averages 327 pounds. High weight goes to left 
tackle Leonard Davis, 6-6, 367 pounds. ... Iowa State has two wins 
in a row over rival Iowa for the first time since a three-game 
streak from 1980-82. The Cyclones are 2-0 for the first time since 
1985. ... Could be lots of scoring when Kansas plays Colorado. Last 
week, the Jayhawks won 71-14 over I-AA Cal State-Northridge; the 
Buffaloes beat San Jose State 63-35. ... Colorado set four school 
records in its win over San Jose State. Mike Moschetti set two (465 
yards passing; 499 total yards); the Buffs set a third with 767 
total yards; and both teams totaled a record 1,205 yards. ... 
Tracey Wistrom, brother of former Huskers All-America Grant 
Wistrom, became the first Nebraska tight end since Johnny Mitchell 
in 1991 to have 100 yards receiving. Wistrom caught two passes for 
109 yards in last week's 45-0 win over Cal. ... Texas QB Major 
Applewhite moved ahead of Bobby Layne into fifth place on the 
Longhorns' career passing chart. Applewhite, a sophomore, has 
thrown for 3,336 yards. Layne threw for 3,145 in four years 
(1944-47). 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                          *Conference USA    	
</P>
<P>
	Louisville QB Chris Redman, with 238 yards and two TDs in last  
week's 58-30 win over Tennessee-Chattanooga, moved into 19th place 
on the NCAA's career passing list (9,456 yards). ... Southern 
Mississippi scored six different ways in beating Northwestern State 
40-6. The Eagles scored on a run, pass, blocked field goal return, 
fumble return, field goal and blocked PAT returned for two points 
.... Houston is back at Legion Field on Sept. 25 to play 
Alabama-Birmingham. The Cougars might fare better than they did 
last week on the same field, losing to Alabama, 37-10. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                               *SEC    	
</P>
<P>
	Kent has the longest losing streak among major colleges at 15  
games, with South Carolina next at 12 straight losses. Lou Holtz's 
Gamecocks will be hard-pressed to avoid No. 13 when East Carolina 
(2-0) visits Williams-Brice Stadium. ``Losing can become a habit 
the same as winning can,'' Holtz said. ``Sometimes things don't fit 
and you start blaming players and coaches and teams and officials 
and everything else. ... You try and build on the positive.'' ... 
For the eighth straight season, Alabama starts 2-0. ... The SEC 
team with the best September record during the 1990s is Florida, at 
30-3. ... Florida, which plays Tennessee on Saturday, faces a 
defending national champion for the 11th time -- the fifth in 
Gainesville. The Gators are 1-7-2 with the lone win 28-13 over 
Alabama in the 1993 SEC title game. ... The Gators are 55-2 at The 
Swamp since 1990, including a 31-1 mark against SEC teams. They 
currently own a 29-game home winning streak. ... For the first time 
since 1981, Mississippi, Mississippi State and Southern Mississippi 
(C-USA) are all 2-0. In '98, all three went to a bowl for the first 
time in the same season. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
                              *Pac-10    	
</P>
<P>
	Believe it or not, Oregon State (2-0) has the league's longest  
current winning streak at three games. The last time the Beavers 
won three straight was 1970, also the last time they posted a 
winning season. ... Washington State (0-2) has a great chance to 
end its 10-game losing streak on Saturday against Idaho. The 
Cougars, whose last win came against the Vandals in '98, have won 
14 in a row against neighboring Idaho and lead the series 63-15-3. 
... UCLA will be at full strength -- the handicapped-parking scam 
suspensions are over -- for the first time when the Bruins play host 
to Fresno State. QB Cory Paus has been declared UCLA's starter, 
beating out Drew Bennett for the job. ``I want to go with one 
quarterback. I'm not going to have a quick trigger,'' UCLA coach 
Bob Toledo says. ... Washington goes for win No. 600 against Air 
Force. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *QUOTING:* ``He thinks he's great at everything, and he may be  
right. He could have been a starting wide receiver and a starting 
safety and been all-Pac-10 in all of them, maybe All-American.'' -- 
Arizona State coach Bruce Snyder on TB J.R. Redmond, the Sun 
Devils' offensive star who played seven positions at Carson 
(Calif.) HS. 
  	   	
</P>
