<HEADLINE> D-Backs' Williams Takes Leave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- National League RBIs leader Matt Williams has  
left the Arizona Diamondbacks to be with his family in Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
	Diamondbacks manager Buck Showalter said Williams told him about  
a serious illness in his family on Sunday, and caught a flight to 
Carson City, Nev., on Tuesday along with his children and his wife, 
actress Michelle Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	``He said, `In my gut I feel like I have to be there,' and I  
said, `Get the hell out of here,' '' manager Buck Showalter said 
before Tuesday night's game against Pittsburgh. 
</P>
