<HEADLINE> Nokia Gets Picus Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HELSINKI, Finland (AP) -- Finnish telecommunications company  
Nokia has won a three-year contract to supply equipment to 
Virginia-based Picus Communications for a network that delivers 
high-speed data and voice services. 
</P>
<P>
	The first phase of the contract is valued at $76 million and  
will involve digital subscriber lines in a number of Virginia 
cities, including Richmond and Norfolk, and Washington D.C., the 
Finnish company said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal will allow Picus to deploy up to 1.1 million digital  
subscriber lines to small and medium-size businesses and 
residential users, Nokia said. 
</P>
<P>
	Nokia is a world leader in digital mobile phone technology with  
sales in 130 countries and 51,000 workers. 
</P>
<P>
	Nokia, the world's largest mobile phone maker, had a net profit  
of $1.14 billion during the first six months of the year. 



  	   	
</P>
