<HEADLINE> 2nd Press Aide Leaves Dole Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- A second press aide to Elizabeth Dole quit,  
her campaign said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Press secretary Michael Paranzino submitted his resignation for  
personal reasons shortly after the Aug. 14 Iowa straw poll and left 
last week, said communications director Ari Fleischer. 
</P>
<P>
	Fleischer announced his own resignation late last week but said  
he did not mention Paranzino's departure at the same time because, 
``I didn't think it rose to the level of news.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fleischer said both he and Paranzino remain confident in Dole's  
candidacy. 
</P>
<P>
	Paranzino, one in a press operation of four, was Dole's  
traveling companion and most visible aide out on the stump. ``In 
retrospect, we probably made a mistake asking a married guy to live 
his life on the road,'' said Fleischer, referring to Paranzino. 
  	   	
</P>
