<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Tuesday, Sept. 14, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Down 120.00  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks tumbled today after reports of  
strong retail sales and a soaring trade deficit reignited fears 
that interest rates will rise. The dollar continued to slip, adding 
to the pressure on stocks. At the close of trading on Wall Street, 
the Dow Jones industrial average was down 120.00 at 10,910.33. 
Broader stock indicators turned mixed. The Nasdaq composite index 
rose 23.51 to 2,868.28. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,910.33  - 120.00
