<HEADLINE> Columbia Tri-Star TV Chief Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Columbia TriStar Television President Jon  
Feltheimer has resigned, days after parent company Sony Pictures 
Entertainment rehired former TV chief Mel Harris. 
</P>
<P>
	Feltheimer's contract was to expire in February, and his future  
had been uncertain after Harris was appointed last week as 
co-president and chief operating officer of Sony Pictures 
Entertainment. Harris, who had left Sony in 1995, was brought back 
to oversee television production. 
</P>
<P>
	Under Feltheimer, Columbia TriStar had produced such hits as  
``Mad About You,'' ``The Nanny'' and ``Party of Five.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Feltheimer joined the company in 1991 as president of TriStar  
television and became head of Columbia TriStar in 1994, when the 
two TV divisions were merged. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
