<HEADLINE> Irvine To Drive for Jaguar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- Jaguar is going into Formula One  
racing next year with Eddie Irvine and Johnny Herbert as drivers. 
</P>
<P>
	Ford recently purchased Jackie Stewart's team for $160 million,  
and the former three-time Formula One champion will head Jaguar 
racing. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine is replacing Rubens Barrichello, who is going to Ferrari  
from Stewart-Ford. 
</P>
<P>
	The move allows Irvine to finally become the No. 1 driver for a  
team after being second to Michael Schumacher at Ferrari for three 
years. 
</P>
<P>
	When Schumacher broke his leg this summer in a crash at the  
British Grand Prix, Irvine took over the No. 1 role, but with the 
understanding it would be only until Schumacher was able to reclaim 
it. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvine has a chance to become the first Ferrari driver in 20  
years to win the championship. 
</P>
<P>
	With three races left on the Grand Prix circuit, Irvine is tied  
with defending champion Mika Hakkinen of McLaren-Mercedes at 60 
points. 
</P>
<P>
	Herbert already has driving for Stewart-Ford.  
</P>
<P>
	Stewart said he had always hoped that Jaguar would become  
involved in Formula One once Ford had bought out his team. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
