<HEADLINE> Groin Sidelines Slugger McGwire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire missed a chance to gain on Sammy  
Sosa in the home-run race Tuesday, sitting out with an injured left 
groin. 
</P>
<P>
	The St. Louis Cardinals' first baseman left Monday night's game  
after 4 1-2 innings. He injured the groin compensating for a stiff 
back and may miss Wednesday's game as well. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's still got a little pinch in there,'' manager Tony La  
Russa said. ``If I had to bet a dollar, I'd say Friday'' as the day 
he'll be back. The Cardinals are off Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	With 55 homers, McGwire was four behind Sosa. He finished four  
ahead of Sosa in his record 70-homer season last year. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has played 138 games and had been tied for the team lead  
with utility player Joe McEwing, who started in left field Tuesday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	Eduardo Perez hit for McGwire in the fifth Monday and was  
2-for-3, his first hits with the Cardinals. Perez started at first 
base Tuesday and batted fifth, with Fernando Tatis taking McGwire's 
No. 3 slot. 
</P>
<P>
	Perez, son of former Cincinnati Reds great Tony Perez, was  
called up Sept. 1 from Triple-A Memphis, where he hit .320 with 18 
homers and 82 RBIs. He had only two at-bats with the Cardinals 
before Tuesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
