<DOCNO> APW19990914.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 08:30:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Web Site Defaced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PRETORIA, South Africa (AP) --Hackers defaced the Web site of  
South Africa's national statistics agency by inserting obscenities 
and a lewd graphic onto its homepage, the government agency said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials of the agency linked the electronic vandalism to a  
labor dispute at the state telecommunications company, Telkom. The 
obscenities were directed at Telkom, whose subsidiary manages the 
agency's server, said Statistics South Africa's director of 
publishing, Glenn Moss. 
</P>
<P>
	Telkom has been locked in a bitter struggle with its unions,  
which went on strike Aug. 16. But Telkom rejected the notion that 
the hacking was connected to the strike. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's got absolutely nothing to do with the labor action,''  
said company spokeswoman Amanda Singleton. She suggested the 
tampering was more probably the work of young teen-age hackers, who 
in the past have sent similarly worded abuse to Telkom. 
</P>
<P>
	Statistics SA said the electronic vandalism probably took place  
Saturday night, and was not discovered by the agency until Monday 
morning. Technicians were still trying to restore a cleaned-up home 
page on Tuesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990914.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 06:50:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Computer Snags Threaten Hershey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- Hershey Food Corp. says computer problems  
are making it miss filling some candy orders, threatening Halloween 
deliveries, one of the company's busiest times of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	Kenneth L. Wolfe, chairman and chief executive, said Monday that  
deliveries would be not be back on schedule until mid-October, the 
height of the Halloween candy sales season. 
</P>
<P>
	``While order patterns have remained strong, we have been unable  
to fill them completely, in a timely fashion,'' Wolfe said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	John M. McMillin, who follows the food industry for Prudential  
Securities Inc., said having such problems fall during a busy 
season is especially damaging. 
</P>
<P>
	``For a candy company to miss part of Halloween is not as bad as  
a toy company missing part of Christmas, but it's close,'' McMillin 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said its earnings would be below the expected level  
for the third quarter that ends Oct. 4 and the entire fiscal year 
because of the delivery system problems that were caused by a 
computer system failure. 
</P>
<P>
	The chocolate maker said earnings for the fiscal year that ends  
Jan. 4, 2000, could be 8 percent to 10 percent below previous 
projections of $2.40 per share. The firm declined to project 
earnings for the third quarter. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
