<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Seagate Cutting 10 Percent of Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SCOTTS VALLEY, Calif. (AP) -- Seagate Technology Inc. plans to  
cut about 8,000 jobs, or 10 percent of its work force, over the 
next nine months as it undergoes a restructuring. 
</P>
<P>
	The changes will lower quarterly earnings by up to $200 million,  
the company announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Once complete, the restructuring will save the company $150  
million a year, said spokeswoman Julie Still. 
</P>
<P>
	The work force reduction would be met by attrition, voluntary  
separation incentives and layoffs, she added. 
</P>
<P>
	Seagate Technology Inc. is the world's largest manufacturer of  
computer disc drives, magnetic discs and read-write heads. It also 
makes tape drives, and is a leading developer of business software. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
