<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Packers Sign Veteran Punter Aguiar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- The Green Bay Packers shored up their  
kicking game Tuesday by signing veteran free agent punter Louie 
Aguiar. 
</P>
<P>
	The Packers have been without a dependable punter since veteran  
Sean Landeta signed with the Philadelphia Eagles early in the 
offseason. Green Bay drafted Josh Bidwell in the fourth round, but 
lost the rookie for the season when doctors discovered he had 
testicular cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for the 33-year-old Aguiar, rookie punter Chris  
Hanson was waived. Hanson, who was acquired the same day Bidwell's 
cancer was diagnosed, punted poorly in the Packers' 28-24 victory 
over Oakland on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Aguiar was waived by Kansas City on Sept. 5 after five seasons  
with the Chiefs. He kicked inconsistently last year and lost his 
job in training camp to rookie Daniel Pope. 
</P>
<P>
	Aguiar also was diagnosed with testicular cancer in March 1998.  
He underwent surgery and 15 radiation treatments later that year 
before returning to average 43 yards per punt last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Aguiar kicked for Packers special teams coach Steve Ortmayer at  
Lambeau Field on Tuesday and was signed in the afternoon. After 
playing at Utah State, he spent the first three seasons of his 
career with the New York Jets. 
</P>
<P>
	He also may be used as the holder for kicker Ryan Longwell.  
Quarterback Doug Pederson, last year's holder, also signed with 
Philadelphia, and Bidwell had been the team's primary holder. 
</P>
<P>
	Aguiar has had only one punt blocked in 631 career attempts. His  
streak of 587 consecutive punts without a block was snapped last 
season, but it still stands as the second longest in NFL history 
behind Dave Jennings (623). 
</P>
<P>
	Aguiar will practice with the Packers on Wednesday. Green Bay  
plays at Detroit on Sunday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
